misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that both a manual flag check (resultIndex == -1) and a break statement are necessary to ensure that only the first occurrence of a target is recorded, potentially because they are unsure if break immediately terminates the loop or if it only exits the current if-block.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: In Java, the break statement immediately terminates the innermost enclosing loop (while, for, or do-while). The additional check if (resultIndex == -1) is redundant because the break ensures that the loop body will never execute again for subsequent matches.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No functional error in this case, but it demonstrates a misunderstanding of the efficiency and behavior of loop control statements.
